title._content: And then the trees fell into the lake

description._content: On the shores of Lake Wanaka on the South Island of New Zealand.

The Falls of Ouzoud are the second largest in Africa and are over 100m high. This photo shows the top section of the falls and the famous rainbow, which is, during daylight a virtually permanent phenomena caused by the spray from the falls.

A tiny badger cub at my local sett; taken last August but not uploaded previously. A friend of mine, Howard Birley, is working on an ongoing wildlife project here in Cambridgeshire. The project is being filmed 24/7 and amongst the wildlife captured so far are several badgers, foxes and a pair of barn owls. The project has captured some fascinating footage (and interaction) of these shy creatures which can be viewed via Howard's Blog: naturestudios.uk/ Interesting stuff and well worth a look if you have a spare few minutes (the badger footage in particular is excellent).
